ortant;line-height: 24px!important;">Hi everyone,</p>
<p style=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;font-size: 16px!important;=
line-height: 24px!important;">This one is a big release =E2=80=94 the bigge=
st since we started this newsletter. v0.5.0 lands the multi-account work we=
 said was coming, and also opens up a whole new surface: <strong style=3D"c=
olor: #000;">Calendar</strong>. Herald is no longer just an email client.</=
p>
<p style=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;font-size: 16px!important;=
line-height: 24px!important;">A bit of plumbing made this possible: mail an=
d calendar share a common notion of source/account that flows through reads=
, search, compose, sync, and writes. One caveat for now =E2=80=94 you still=
 add the mail side and the calendar side as separate sources, even when the=
y come from the same provider, but Herald shows them together under one uni=
fied view. That's the unglamorous half; the visible half is below.</p>
<hr style=3D"color: #000;border: none;border-top: 1px solid #eaeaea;border-=
color: #f5f5f5;border-width: 2px;width: 300px;margin: 40px auto;"><h2 style=
=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;">Multi-account, finally</h2>
<p style=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;font-size: 16px!important;=
line-height: 24px!important;">The v0.4 newsletter said this was next. It is=
 now in. You get source badges on messages so you can see at a glance which=
 account a thread came from, Mail.app-style account sections in the folder =
list, account-scoped signatures, and Compose that routes replies from the r=
ight address automatically. Adding and managing accounts happens in Setting=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;font-size: 16px!important;=
line-height: 24px!important;">If you were juggling separate config files an=
d separate terminal windows as the workaround =E2=80=94 you can stop.</p>
<p style=3D"color: #000;margin: 16px 0!important;font-size: 16px!important;=
line-height: 24px!important;">Demo mode now ships with multiple synthetic a=
ccounts too, so you can try the whole multi-account experience =E2=80=94 ba=
dges, sections, Compose routing =E2=80=94 without setting up a single real =
one.</p>
